The paper deals with a geometric optimization problem involving line segments and unit squares in the plane, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The use of approximation algorithms and NP-completeness results suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), and game theory (cs.GT).
